<i>adverb</i>: 순순히 [순ː순히], 빤히 [빤ː히], 담담히 [담ː담히], 꾸밈없이 [꾸미멉씨] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>순순히 [순ː순히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. obediently</dd><br>
<dd>성질이나 태도가 매우 부드럽고 온순하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that the personality or attitude of someone is very tender and docile.</dd><br>
<dd>2. plainly</dd><br>
<dd>음식의 맛이 자극적이지 않고 순하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that the taste of food is not strong but mild.</dd><br>
<dt>빤히 [빤ː히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. brightly</dd><br>
<dd>어둠 속에서 밝은 빛이 비치어 환하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being slightly bright as a light shines in darkness.</dd><br>
<dd>2. plainly; obviously</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일의 결과나 상태가 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which the result or state of something is clear.</dd><br>
<dd>3. fixedly; steadily; intently</dd><br>
<dd>바라보는 것이 정면으로 또렷하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's staring eyes being clear.</dd><br>
<dt>담담히 [담ː담히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. composedly; calmly</dd><br>
<dd>차분하고 편안하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a calm and comfortable attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>2. plainly</dd><br>
<dd>글이나 말 내용이 감정적이지 않고 객관적이게.</dd><br>
<dd>Objectively, not expressing oneself emotionally in writing or speaking.</dd><br>
<dd>3. serenely</dd><br>
<dd>물이 맑고 그 움직임이 고요하고 평온하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state such as that when clean water flows quietly and peacefully.</dd><br>
<dd>4. plainly</dd><br>
<dd>맛이 짜거나 느끼하지 않고 산뜻하고 싱겁게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of tasting fresh and insipid, not salty or greasy.</dd><br>
<dt>꾸밈없이 [꾸미멉씨]</dt><br>
<dd>plainly; frankly</dd><br>
<dd>보기 좋고 그럴듯하게 만드는 것 없이 있는 그대로 진실되게.</dd><br>
<dd>Truthfully in the manner of showing something as it is without making it look good.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>